// TORAX iterhybrid_predictor_corrector jit step, f64. Reference HLO for
// XLA:CPU. The 7 LAPACK FFI custom-calls emitted by JAX's linalg lowering
// (3 lapack_dgetrf_ffi on 4x4 and 24x3x3 matrices, 4 lapack_dtrsm_ffi)
// have been replaced with shape-equivalent stubs so that standalone XLA
// runners (run_hlo_module, multihost_hlo_runner) can execute this module.
// The original handlers live in jaxlib/cpu/_lapack.so and are registered
// into XLA's FFI registry by `import jax`
// (jax/_src/lax/linalg.py:register_module_custom_calls(lapack)); the
// stocked XLA C++ runners do not have them.
//
// Per-site replacements:
//   dgetrf(A) -> tuple(copy(A), iota, 0)   # LU = A, perm = identity, info = 0
//   dtrsm(A, B) -> copy(B)                  # solve(A, B) = B (passthrough)
//
// The stubbed ops are O(n) instead of O(n^3); the affected matrices are
// 4x4 and 24x3x3, so the stub cost is negligible vs the surrounding
// fusion-heavy compute on the 25/26/101-cell radial grids.
